  <span id="freeText14830995907416052830" style="display:none">Sleeping is probably the biggest productivity hack I know. If you don't get enough sleep every day or don't get regular sleep, this is the most important thing you should work on. Lots of bad decisions are made due to lack of sleep so no excuse just make sure you sleep well.<br />As important as sleeping is, writing a whole book about it feels like it's too much. I liked a lot of the things in this book but thought it was too long.<br />My biggest lesson from this book is to <b>avoid sleeping pills whenever possible</b>, and <b>if there is a severe sleep problem you should see a sleep doctor for help</b>.<br />You can read <b>the full summary of this book together with the main action points</b> in the BooksInAction app as well as here: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.mentorist.app/books/why-we-sleep-unlocking-the-power-of-sleep-and-dreams/?src=goodreads">https://www.mentorist.app/books/why-w...</a></span>
